<h1>KiteAI X Agent — Complete Workflow (Updated)</h1>
<p style="color:#555;font-size:10pt">
API: twitter241.p.rapidapi.com &nbsp;|&nbsp; AI: Gemini 2.5 Flash via OpenRouter (fallback: Claude Haiku 4.5) &nbsp;|&nbsp;
Schedule: Weekly Monday 02:00 IST &nbsp;|&nbsp; Cap: 5,000 req/run &nbsp;|&nbsp; ~1,000-1,200 new accounts/run
</p>

<div class="box-y" style="margin-bottom:20pt">
<b>What changed from previous version:</b>
<ul>
<li>Compound OR keyword queries (4-5 keywords per search call → 358 searches → ~90 calls)</li>
<li>Pagination cursor used (page 2 of search results per query)</li>
<li>Weekly rotation: 1/4 of keywords per run (auto runs only)</li>
<li>Cross-query frequency sorting (accounts appearing in multiple searches fetched first)</li>
<li>Track A1/A2 classification fully integrated into agent fetch (no separate button)</li>
<li>All AI scoring switched to Gemini 2.5 Flash (fallback Claude Haiku 4.5)</li>
<li>Evidence-based paid-post pattern detector (regex signals + Gemini, quoted evidence)</li>
<li>Resolve Unknowns backfill — re-classify the unknown/none Track A backlog into A1/A2</li>
<li>Stale unknown/none duplicates re-checked on every refresh run</li>
<li>Dashboard Last Run Summary card (fetched + A1/A2/B/Other split, from run_id)</li>
<li>A2 content-authenticity scoring (0-100): split A2 into ✦ Genuine vs ⚠ Salesy creators</li>
<li>Brand ambassador exclusion (not available for our collab)</li>
<li>DB-level sort: A1 → A2 → Unknown in Track A endpoint</li>
<li>~1,000-1,200 new accounts per full run</li>
</ul>
</div>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 1 — TRIGGER</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Type</th><th>How</th><th>Details</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>Manual</b></td><td>Click "Run Agent" on dashboard</td><td>GET /api/run-demo (JWT), full run all queries, results stream live via SSE</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Weekly Auto</b></td><td>node-cron: 0 2 * * 1</td><td>Every Monday 02:00 AM IST. Uses weekly rotation (1/4 of queries per run). triggeredBy='weekly_cron'</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 2 — KEYWORD LOADING &amp; COMPOUND QUERY BUILDING</h2>
<h3>Own Keywords (61) + Friend DB (up to 300)</h3>
<pre>Own DB:    61 keywords → Class C (Voice AI), A (Models), B (Orchestration), E/F/H/K
Friend DB: up to 300 search_query fields (High priority first)
Direct:    42 influencer handles (fetched directly, skip search step)

Total: ~358 queries merged and deduplicated</pre>

<h3>Compound OR Query Building (NEW)</h3>
<p>Instead of 358 separate API calls, keywords are grouped into compound OR queries:</p>
<pre>BEFORE (inefficient):
  Search 1: "vapi"             → 1 call
  Search 2: "elevenlabs"       → 1 call
  Search 3: "deepgram"         → 1 call
  Search 4: "retell ai"        → 1 call
  = 4 calls, overlapping results

AFTER (compound OR):
  Search 1: "vapi OR elevenlabs OR deepgram OR retell ai"  → 1 call
  = 1 call, broader results, ~75% fewer search calls

358 keywords ÷ 4 per group = ~90 compound queries
Savings: ~268 fewer search calls → freed for profile fetches</pre>

<h3>Weekly Rotation (auto-runs only)</h3>
<pre>weekSlot = Math.floor((date.getDate() - 1) / 7) % 4
Week 1: queries at index 0, 4, 8, 12...  (~22 queries)
Week 2: queries at index 1, 5, 9, 13...  (~22 queries)
Week 3: queries at index 2, 6, 10, 14... (~22 queries)
Week 4: queries at index 3, 7, 11, 15... (~22 queries)

Effect: 4× more profile fetch budget per weekly run
Manual runs: always use full ~90 compound queries</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 3 — SEARCH API CALL (twitter241)</h2>
<h3>Exact Request String</h3>
<pre>GET https://twitter241.p.rapidapi.com/search?query=vapi+OR+elevenlabs+OR+deepgram+OR+%22retell+ai%22&count=47&type=Top

Headers:
  X-RapidAPI-Key:  YOUR_RAPIDAPI_PAID_KEY_HERE
  X-RapidAPI-Host: twitter241.p.rapidapi.com
  Content-Type:    application/json

Parameters:
  query = "vapi OR elevenlabs OR deepgram OR "retell ai""
  count = 47   ← varies 40-50 each call (anti-bot)
  type  = "Top" ← most relevant results

URL-encoded: spaces → +, quotes → %22</pre>

<h3>Pagination (Page 2)</h3>
<pre>After page 1 response, extract cursor:
  response.cursor.bottom = "DAACCgACHJ..."

Page 2 request:
GET https://twitter241.p.rapidapi.com/search?query=vapi+OR+elevenlabs+...&count=47&type=Top&cursor=DAACCgACHJ...

Effect: 2× handles from one keyword group = ~180 handles per compound query</pre>

<h3>Search Response Structure</h3>
<pre>{
  "cursor": {
    "bottom": "DAACCgACHJypbe2AJxAK...",    ← use for page 2
    "top":    "DAACCgACHJypbe2AJxAK..."
  },
  "result": {
    "timeline": {
      "instructions": [
        {
          "type": "TimelineAddEntries",      ← look for this
          "entries": [
            {
              "content": {
                "itemContent": {
                  "tweet_results": {
                    "result": {
                      "core": {
                        "user_results": {
                          "result": {
                            "core": {
                              "screen_name": "vapidev",  ← EXTRACTED
                              "name": "Vapi"
                            }
                          }
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}</pre>

<h3>What We Extract from Search</h3>
<p>ONLY the <code>screen_name</code> (handle) from each tweet entry. Everything else is ignored.</p>
<pre>extractHandles241(data):
  → find instructions entry where type === "TimelineAddEntries"
  → loop entries[]
  → path: entry.content.itemContent.tweet_results.result.core.user_results.result.core.screen_name
  → deduplicate within query (seenQuery Set)
  → deduplicate across all queries this run (seenThisRun Set)
  → sort by cross-query frequency (accounts in 3+ searches fetched first)</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 4 — RATE LIMITER &amp; ANTI-BOT</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Setting</th><th>Value</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>Key</td><td>KeyPaid (twitter241)</td><td>Paid shared key — 100K/month</td></tr>
<tr><td>RPM</td><td>3 req/minute</td><td>Conservative — 20s min gap between requests</td></tr>
<tr><td>Jitter</td><td>±3,000ms random</td><td>No mechanical 20s pattern</td></tr>
<tr><td>Human break</td><td>30-60s every 20-35 requests</td><td>Simulates human browsing behaviour</td></tr>
<tr><td>Query shuffle</td><td>Random order each run</td><td>No predictable sequence</td></tr>
<tr><td>Count variation</td><td>40-50 per search (random)</td><td>Never always the same number</td></tr>
<tr><td>Run cap</td><td>5,000 requests max</td><td>Protects shared quota</td></tr>
<tr><td>SSE keepalive</td><td>: ping every 5s</td><td>Prevents Render dropping connection</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 5 — PROFILE FETCH (twitter241)</h2>
<h3>Exact Request String</h3>
<pre>GET https://twitter241.p.rapidapi.com/user?username=vapidev

Headers:
  X-RapidAPI-Key:  YOUR_RAPIDAPI_PAID_KEY_HERE
  X-RapidAPI-Host: twitter241.p.rapidapi.com

Parameter:
  username = "vapidev"   ← no @ symbol, just the handle</pre>

<h3>Profile Response Structure</h3>
<pre>{
  "result": {
    "data": {
      "user": {
        "result": {
          "core": {
            "screen_name": "vapidev",                     ← handle
            "name":        "Vapi",                        ← display name
            "created_at":  "Mon Jan 09 2023"
          },
          "legacy": {
            "description":     "Build voice AI apps. DM for partnerships.",  ← bio
            "followers_count": 12400,
            "friends_count":   890,                       ← following
            "statuses_count":  1240,                      ← tweet count
            "location":        "San Francisco",
            "entities": {
              "url": {
                "urls": [{ "expanded_url": "https://vapi.ai" }]  ← website
              }
            }
          },
          "is_blue_verified": true,                       ← verified
          "avatar": {
            "image_url": "https://pbs.twimg.com/..."      ← profile photo
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}</pre>

<h3>Field Mapping</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Our field</th><th>twitter241 path</th><th>Example</th></tr>
<tr><td>name</td><td>result.core.name</td><td>"Vapi"</td></tr>
<tr><td>handle</td><td>result.core.screen_name</td><td>"vapidev"</td></tr>
<tr><td>bio</td><td>result.legacy.description</td><td>"Build voice AI apps..."</td></tr>
<tr><td>followers</td><td>result.legacy.followers_count</td><td>12400</td></tr>
<tr><td>following</td><td>result.legacy.friends_count</td><td>890</td></tr>
<tr><td>tweets</td><td>result.legacy.statuses_count</td><td>1240</td></tr>
<tr><td>verified</td><td>result.is_blue_verified</td><td>true</td></tr>
<tr><td>avatar</td><td>result.avatar.image_url</td><td>"https://pbs.twimg..."</td></tr>
<tr><td>website</td><td>result.legacy.entities.url.urls[0].expanded_url</td><td>"https://vapi.ai"</td></tr>
<tr><td>location</td><td>result.legacy.location</td><td>"San Francisco"</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>6-Day Skip Optimisation</h3>
<pre>Before fetching profile:
  Check DB: SELECT handle FROM accounts WHERE handle IN (...) AND last_updated > (now - 6 days)
  Handles updated within 6 days → SKIP (save API quota on weekly re-runs)

Effect on weekly re-runs: most handles already fresh → only 100-200 new fetches
Effect on first run: all handles are new → full ~2,400 fetches</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 6 — PROFILE VALIDATION</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Rule</th><th>Discard if</th><th>Why</th></tr>
<tr><td>Follower minimum</td><td>followers &lt; 100</td><td>Bot / new empty account</td></tr>
<tr><td>Activity</td><td>tweets &lt; 1</td><td>Never posted</td></tr>
<tr><td>Name check</td><td>name is empty</td><td>Suspended account</td></tr>
<tr><td>Bio + reach</td><td>followers &lt; 500 AND bio empty</td><td>No signal at all</td></tr>
<tr><td>Post-score gate</td><td>overall &lt; 10</td><td>Zero relevance</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 7 — SCORING (D2–D5)</h2>
<h3>D4 — Authority (20% weight, instant)</h3>
<pre>D4 = min(95, verified_bonus + ratio_bonus + follower_bonus)

verified_bonus: +30 if blue_verified

ratio_bonus (followers ÷ following):
  ≥ 30x → +35  |  ≥ 10x → +22  |  ≥ 3x → +12  |  else +0

follower_bonus:
  ≥ 100,000 → +30  |  ≥ 10,000 → +20  |  ≥ 1,000 → +10  |  else +0

Example @vapidev: verified(+30) + ratio 13.9x(+22) + 10K+(+20) = 72</pre>

<h3>D5 — Reach Quality (30% weight, instant)</h3>
<pre>≥ 500,000 → Macro    → D5 = 95
≥ 100,000 → Mid-Tier → D5 = 80
≥  10,000 → Micro    → D5 = 60
≥   1,000 → Nano     → D5 = 40
≥     500 → Low      → D5 = 25
&lt;     500 → Very Low → D5 = 10</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 8 — GEMINI 2.5 FLASH BATCH SCORING (D2 + D3 + Classification)</h2>
<h3>What the Model Does</h3>
<p>Reads bio + name for 6 accounts simultaneously. Returns D2, D3, type, track, AND promotion classification.</p>

<h3>Input Sent to the Model (6 accounts per call)</h3>
<pre>POST https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions
{
  "model": "google/gemini-2.5-flash",   // fallback: anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5
  "max_tokens": 750,
  "temperature": 0.1,
  "messages": [{
    "role": "user",
    "content": "KiteAI — voice AI company. Score these X accounts.

D2 Collab Intent (0-100):
  90+: DM open/media kit/email in bio
  65-89: website/biz inquiries
  35-64: personal no signals
  10-34: news/corp brand
  0-9: bot/spam

D3 AI Relevance (0-100):
  90+: voice AI/LLM/Vapi/ElevenLabs builder
  65-89: AI founder/SaaS/creator
  35-64: general tech
  10-34: adjacent
  0-9: none

type: Influencer | PR Page | AI Media | Brand Page | Account
track: A=collab pipeline | B=ads audience only

PROMOTION DETECTION:
promotion_type: explicit|inferred|none|unknown
  explicit = bio says paid work: DM for sponsorships, media kit, UGC creator, collab@email
  inferred = profile PATTERN suggests paid: lifestyle creator, reviewer, multiple brand signals
  (NOT explicit: brand ambassador for one brand = exclusive, not available for us)
promotion_confidence: 0-100
promotion_signals: array of 3 detected signals

ACCOUNTS:
1. @vapidev | Vapi | 12,400 followers | verified:yes | bio: Build voice AI. DM for partnerships.
2. @swyx    | swyx | 162,000 followers | verified:yes | bio: AI dev education, founder
[...4 more accounts...]

Return ONLY JSON array, same order. No markdown."
  }]
}</pre>

<h3>Response from the Model</h3>
<pre>[
  {"d2":88,"d3":95,"type":"Brand Page","track":"A",
   "promotion_type":"explicit","promotion_confidence":90,
   "promotion_signals":["DM for partnerships in bio"]},
  {"d2":72,"d3":88,"type":"Influencer","track":"A",
   "promotion_type":"inferred","promotion_confidence":65,
   "promotion_signals":["content creator pattern","tech educator"]},
  ...
]</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 9 — TRACK A PROMOTION CLASSIFICATION (A1/A2)</h2>
<p>After AI scoring, every Track A account goes through the evidence-based paid-post detector automatically during the fetch — no separate step.</p>

<h3>3-Phase Flow (inline during agent run)</h3>
<pre>Phase 1 — Exclusion check (free, instant):
  "Official X ambassador" → skip A1/A2 (exclusive to one brand, not available for us)
  "Ambassador @brand" → skip
  "Brand ambassador for Y" → skip
  These accounts can't promote KiteAI — they work for one brand only

Phase 2 — Bio keyword check (free, instant):
  EXPLICIT signals → A1 immediately (no tweet needed):
    "DM for collabs", "DM for paid promo", "open to brand deals"
    "media kit", "UGC creator", "content creator for hire"
    collab@email, partnerships@email
    #ad or #sponsored in bio

  INFERRED signals → A2 pending tweet check:
    "content creator", "lifestyle blogger", "digital creator"
    "affiliate", "youtuber", "opinions are my own"

Phase 3 — Paid-post pattern detector (1 extra API call, only if needed):
  Fires for: Track A accounts without explicit bio signal
    (incl. stale unknown/none duplicates re-checked on refresh)
  Skips: accounts where bio already confirmed A1
  Fetches 20 recent ORIGINAL posts (retweets skipped) via:
    GET /search?query=from:vapidev&count=20&type=Latest</pre>

<h3>Tweet Analysis — Request String</h3>
<pre>GET https://twitter241.p.rapidapi.com/search?query=from%3Ahasantoxr&count=20&type=Latest

Headers:
  X-RapidAPI-Key:  YOUR_RAPIDAPI_PAID_KEY_HERE
  X-RapidAPI-Host: twitter241.p.rapidapi.com

URL-encoded: from:hasantoxr → from%3Ahasantoxr</pre>

<h3>Paid-Post Pattern Detector — Gemini Prompt</h3>
<pre>You are a sponsored-content detector for KiteAI (hires influencers for PAID promotions).
GOAL: Decide if @hasantoxr takes money/products to promote OTHER companies' products.

Bio: "Helping you master AI daily with step-by-step AI guides..."
Auto-detected signals -> disclosures:1 codes:1 affiliate:0 giveaways:0 brand+CTA:2 | distinct brands:3
Recent posts (20 original, retweets skipped):
1. "Use code HASAN10 for 20% off at @BrandA..."
2. "Honest review of @ProductB after 2 weeks, try it..."
3. "Partnered with @BrandC this week #ad..."
[...20 posts total]

HOW A PAID POST LOOKS:
  PAID:     code/affiliate/#ad for someone else, OR 2+ different brands with CTAs
  NOT PAID: technical threads, OR promoting only their OWN product

RULES (no compromise):
  explicit = >=1 post has a clear disclosure (#ad/#sponsored) OR a code/affiliate for another brand
  inferred = no tag, but a pattern: >=2 different brands w/ CTAs, or a brand giveaway
  none     = technical/research/journalism, OR only their own product
  unknown  = too few posts / no signal — do NOT guess
  EVERY explicit/inferred verdict MUST quote the exact post that proves it

Return ONLY JSON:
{"promotion_type":"explicit"|"inferred"|"none"|"unknown","confidence":0-100,"signals":["<reason + quoted post>"],"brands":["@b1","@b2"]}</pre>

<h3>Cheap Regex Pre-Scan (free, before the AI)</h3>
<pre>Each post is scanned for signals first (no API/AI cost):
  DISCLOSURE -> A1:  #ad  #sponsored  "paid partnership"  "sponsored by"
  CODE -> A2:        "use code X"  "20% off"  promo/discount/coupon code
  AFFILIATE -> A2:   ?ref=  utm_  amzn.to  bit.ly  "link in bio to shop"
  GIVEAWAY -> A2:    "giveaway"  "RT + follow to win"  "enter to win"
  BRAND+CTA -> A2:   @mention + (try|sign up|get yours|shop|grab|claim)
  + counts DISTINCT brands across promo posts (>=2 = serial-promoter pattern)

Quality backstops:
  - a real #ad/#sponsored tag can NEVER be rated below A1 (regex override)
  - if the AI call fails -> fall back to these regex signals
  - the counts feed the Gemini prompt as "Auto-detected signals" for calibration</pre>

<h3>Upgrade Logic</h3>
<pre>Bio says "inferred" + tweets say "explicit" → upgrade to A1 (explicit wins)
Bio says "unknown" + tweets say "inferred" → set to A2
Bio says "explicit" → A1, skip tweet fetch entirely (saves 1 API call)
After both checks, still unknown → save to DB as unknown (not shown in A1/A2 filter)</pre>

<h3>Key Distinction — Ambassador vs Available</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Bio says</th><th>Classification</th><th>Why</th></tr>
<tr><td>"DM for collabs"</td><td><span class="tag tag-g">A1 Confirmed</span></td><td>Open to any brand including KiteAI</td></tr>
<tr><td>"open to paid sponsorships"</td><td><span class="tag tag-g">A1 Confirmed</span></td><td>Explicitly available</td></tr>
<tr><td>"Ambassador @glider__ • @cyfrin"</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">Excluded</span></td><td>Works for specific brands — not available for us</td></tr>
<tr><td>"Official Raycon Ambassador"</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">Excluded</span></td><td>Single-brand exclusive</td></tr>
<tr><td>Bio unclear → tweets show #ad</td><td><span class="tag tag-b">A2 Likely</span></td><td>Does paid work, detected via tweets</td></tr>
<tr><td>No signals in bio or tweets</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">Unknown</span></td><td>Saved to DB, hidden from A1/A2 filter</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>STEP 9b — A2 Content Authenticity (Genuine Creators vs Salesy/Templated)</h3>
<p>A2 is split by content quality so it stays a clean list of <b>genuine creators</b> whose product posts an audience would trust — not hyped-up ads or AI/templated spam. Every A2 account gets an <b>authenticity score 0-100</b> (Gemini reading 20 posts, blended 70% AI + 30% regex hint), with the single most genuine post quoted as evidence.</p>
<table>
<tr><th>Signal</th><th>Effect</th><th>Examples</th></tr>
<tr><td>First-person lived experience</td><td><span class="tag tag-g">RAISES</span></td><td>"I've been using…", "switched to…", "after 2 weeks…"</td></tr>
<tr><td>Specific details</td><td><span class="tag tag-g">RAISES</span></td><td>real features, timeframes, concrete use-case</td></tr>
<tr><td>Honest / balanced</td><td><span class="tag tag-g">RAISES</span></td><td>admits a downside, "skeptical at first"</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hype overload</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">LOWERS</span></td><td>ALL CAPS, 🚀🔥, "BEST EVER"</td></tr>
<tr><td>Generic / templated</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">LOWERS</span></td><td>interchangeable praise, repeated structure</td></tr>
<tr><td>Pure CTA / robotic</td><td><span class="tag tag-y">LOWERS</span></td><td>"buy now, link in bio", no personal voice</td></tr>
</table>
<pre>BUCKETS (threshold GENUINE_THRESHOLD = 60):
  ✦ A2 — Genuine    authenticity_score >= 60   (the clean curated list)
  ◷ A2 — Unscored   authenticity_score IS NULL (run Resolve to score)
  ⚠ Salesy / Low    authenticity_score < 60    (separate bucket, nothing lost)

Stored: authenticity_score / authenticity_reason / authenticity_example (quoted post)
Sort within A2: authenticity DESC, then overall.
NOTE: we score genuine-EXPERIENCE quality directly rather than "is it AI-written?" —
research shows off-the-shelf AI-text detection is unreliable and false-flags real people,
so it is only a low-weight proxy.</pre>
<div class="box-g">Worked example: @_akhaliq scored 15 -> Salesy (templated "X just released Y" announcements, not genuine personal reviews). A creator posting "Rebuilt our support line with @Tool — skeptical at first, but it holds a natural conversation. Still wish Hindi was better." scores high -> Genuine.</div>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 10 — FINAL SCORE &amp; TRACK ASSIGNMENT</h2>
<pre style="font-size:13pt;text-align:center">
Overall = D2 × 0.25  +  D3 × 0.25  +  D4 × 0.20  +  D5 × 0.30
</pre>

<h3>Track A Sort Order (DB-level)</h3>
<pre>SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE track='A'
ORDER BY
  CASE promotion_type WHEN 'explicit' THEN 0 WHEN 'inferred' THEN 1 ELSE 2 END,
  overall DESC

Result:
  1st: A1 (💰 Confirmed Paid) → sorted by score
  2nd: A2 (~ Likely Paid)    → sorted by score
  3rd: Unknown               → sorted by score (hidden in UI filters)</pre>

<h3>Track Enforcement</h3>
<pre>finalTrack = (type === 'PR Page' || type === 'Brand Page') ? 'B' : 'A'
AI's track suggestion is ALWAYS overridden by this rule.
Prevents inconsistencies where AI says "PR Page" but returns track "A".</pre>

<h3>Worked Example — @vapidev</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Dim</th><th>Value</th><th>Weight</th><th>Contribution</th><th>Method</th></tr>
<tr><td>D2</td><td>88</td><td>25%</td><td>22.0</td><td>Gemini — "DM for partnerships" = explicit</td></tr>
<tr><td>D3</td><td>95</td><td>25%</td><td>23.75</td><td>Gemini — "Build voice AI apps" = core AI</td></tr>
<tr><td>D4</td><td>72</td><td>20%</td><td>14.4</td><td>Algo — verified+ratio+10K+</td></tr>
<tr><td>D5</td><td>60</td><td>30%</td><td>18.0</td><td>Algo — 12,400 = Micro</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Overall</b></td><td><b>78</b></td><td>100%</td><td><b>78.15</b></td><td>A1, Track A</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 11 — DEDUPLICATION</h2>
<pre>Layer 1 — seenThisRun Set (within one run):
  Handles seen across ALL compound queries tracked in Set
  Same handle in "voice ai OR vapi" AND "ai agent builder OR vapi" → fetched only once

Layer 2 — DB UNIQUE on handle column:
  INSERT OR UPDATE (upsert) — never creates duplicate rows

Layer 3 — 6-day recency skip:
  SQL: SELECT handle FROM accounts WHERE handle IN (...) AND last_updated > (now - 6 days)
  Handles updated within 6 days → skip entirely (saves API quota on weekly re-runs)</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 12 — DATABASE WRITE</h2>
<pre>INSERT INTO accounts (
  handle, name, bio, followers, following, tweets, verified,
  avatar, website, location, tier, account_type, track,
  d2, d3, d4, d5, overall, dm_open, has_email, contact_email,
  ai_model, promotion_type, promotion_confidence, promotion_signals,
  run_id
)

Track B (PR Page/Brand Page): saved for X Ads audience targeting
Track A A1/A2: saved, shown in collab pipeline
Track A Unknown: saved to DB but hidden from A1/A2 filter in UI</pre>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 13 — SSE EVENTS (Real-Time to Browser)</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Event</th><th>When</th><th>Key data</th></tr>
<tr><td>status</td><td>Every step</td><td>step (searching/fetching/tweet_check/pacing/filtered/ai_scoring), message, progress%</td></tr>
<tr><td>search_done</td><td>After each compound query search</td><td>query, found, fetching (new only), rawHandles.length, duration_ms</td></tr>
<tr><td>account</td><td>After each account scored and saved</td><td>Full account: all scores, promotion_type, isDuplicate</td></tr>
<tr><td>fetch_error</td><td>Profile fetch fails</td><td>handle, HTTP status</td></tr>
<tr><td>quota_exhausted</td><td>3 consecutive 429s</td><td>message — resets midnight UTC</td></tr>
<tr><td>complete</td><td>Run finished</td><td>accountsAdded, duplicatesSkipped, totalAccountsInDB, confirmedPaid (A1), likelyPaid (A2)</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="box-y">
Run complete summary example:<br>
<code>Run complete — 45 new added, 12 updated. DB total: 1,072 · 28 confirmed paid (A1) · 41 likely paid (A2)</code>
</div>

