<hr>
<h2>TRACK A/B SUMMARY</h2>
<table>
<tr><th>Track</th><th>Types</th><th>Promotion Status</th><th>Action</th></tr>
<tr><td><b style="color:#065f46">Track A — A1</b></td><td>Influencer, AI Media, Account</td><td>💰 Confirmed paid (explicit bio or tweet signals)</td><td>DM or email — top priority outreach</td></tr>
<tr><td><b style="color:#92400e">Track A — A2</b></td><td>Influencer, AI Media, Account</td><td>~ Likely paid (tweet patterns suggest it)</td><td>DM or email — secondary outreach</td></tr>
<tr><td><b style="color:#555">Track A — Unknown</b></td><td>Any</td><td>? Not yet analysed</td><td>In DB, hidden from filter — will classify on next run</td></tr>
<tr><td><b style="color:#555">Track B</b></td><td>PR Page, Brand Page</td><td>N/A</td><td>NEVER contact — use followers for X Ads targeting</td></tr>
</table>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 12 — RESOLVE UNKNOWNS (On-Demand Backfill)</h2>
<p>Most accounts in the DB predate the paid-post detector and sit as <code>unknown</code>/<code>none</code>. The <b>Resolve Unbadged Accounts</b> button on the Track A page re-runs the detector over the entire backlog (relevant-first) and promotes the real promoters into A1/A2.</p>
<pre>GET /api/resolve-unknowns          (SSE, JWT via _token)

1. SELECT handle, bio FROM accounts WHERE track='A' AND (
     promotion_type IN ('unknown','none')                  &lt;- classify
     OR (promotion_type IN ('inferred','explicit')
         AND authenticity_score IS NULL) )                 &lt;- quality-score A2
   ORDER BY overall DESC            &lt;- most relevant first
2. For each: fetch 20 posts -> analysePaidPattern -> resolve type + score authenticity
3. Idempotent (scored accounts not re-picked) - 3 RPM - 5,000 cap - abortable.
4. Streams a live tally:
   { toA1, toA2, genuine, salesy, toNone, stillUnknown, processed, total }</pre>
<div class="box-g">The live agent does this too: stale <code>unknown</code>/<code>none</code> duplicates are re-checked on every refresh, so the backlog shrinks automatically over time.</div>

<hr>
<h2>STEP 13 — LAST RUN SUMMARY (Dashboard Card)</h2>
<p>The Dashboard shows the most recent run's totals, computed from <code>accounts.run_id</code> (set on every fetch/save) so the numbers stay accurate even if the run record never finalized (e.g. dev restart mid-run).</p>
<pre>GET /api/dashboard/last-run

{ runId, status, totalFetched, newAccounts, updatedAccounts,
  a1, a2, trackB, other }

  totalFetched = COUNT(*) WHERE run_id = lastRunId
  a1 / a2      = run_id=last AND track='A' AND promotion_type = explicit / inferred
  trackB       = run_id=last AND track='B'
  other        = run_id=last AND track='A' AND promotion_type IN (none, unknown)
  newAccounts  = run_id=last AND first_seen &gt;= run.started_at</pre>

